# Branch Naming Conventions

## AI Branch Prefixes
- **Cursor AI**: `cursor/[task-description]` (REQUIRED)
- **Codex AI**: `codex/[task-description]` (RECOMMENDED)

## Standard Prefixes
- `feature/` - New features
- `fix/` - Bug fixes
- `hotfix/` - Critical production fixes
- `chore/` - Maintenance tasks
- `docs/` - Documentation updates
- `test/` - Test improvements
- `refactor/` - Code refactoring

## Guidelines
- Use kebab-case (lowercase with hyphens)
- Be descriptive but concise (max 50 characters)
- Include ticket numbers when applicable
- Avoid special characters except hyphens

## Examples
```bash
cursor/implement-oauth2
codex/optimize-database-queries
feature/PROJ-123-payment-integration
fix/login-validation-error
```

## Permanent Branches
No prefixes required: `main`, `develop`, `master`

## Enforcement

- **Cursor**: Automatically enforced via `.cursor/rules`
- **Codex**: Guided by AGENTS.md and helper tools
- **Git Hooks**: Friendly reminders in pre-push hook
- **Manual**: Use `git branch -m old-name new-name` to rename
